com.hazelcast.jet

Interface IMapJet<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this map
    V - the type of values
    All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.core.BaseMap<K,V>, ConcurrentMap<K,V>, com.hazelcast.core.DistributedObject, com.hazelcast.core.IMap<K,V>, com.hazelcast.map.impl.LegacyAsyncMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>

    public interface IMapJet<K,V>
extends com.hazelcast.core.IMap<K,V>
    A distributed, in-memory concurrent map implementation.

    The entries of the map are distributed across the whole cluster and partitioned by key.

    It's possible to use the map as a data source or sink in a Jet Pipeline, using Sources.map(String) or Sinks.map(String) and the change stream of the map can be read using Sources.mapJournal(String, JournalInitialPosition).

    See Also:
    IMap, Sources.map(String), Sources.mapJournal(String, JournalInitialPosition), (String)
